title.rendered: USA vs UAE, World Cup Qualifiers 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
USA vs UAE, World Cup Qualifiers 2023: Fantasy Team

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable USA & UAE XIs

USA: Sushant Modani, Saiteja Mukkamalla/Steven Taylor, Monank Patel (c & wk), Aaron Jones, Gajanand Singh, Shayan Jahangir, Nisarg Patel, Jasdeep Singh, Nosthush Kenjige, Saurabh Netravalkar, Ali Khan

UAE: Muhammad Waseem (c), Aryan Lakra, Vriitya Aravind (wk), Rameez Shahzad, Asif Khan, Rohan Mustafa, Aayan Afzal Khan, Junaid Siddique, Zahoor Khan, Sanchit Sharma, Karthik Meiyappan

United Cricket Club Ground, Windhoek Pitch Report

Venue: United Cricket Club Ground, Windhoek

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 246

2nd innings average score: 301

Wickets per innings: 8

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Also Read:

Punjab vs Kolkata Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

LSG vs Delhi Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Gujarat vs Chennai Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Vriitya Aravind (213 runs at 53) and Junaid Siddique (seven wickets) are the leading run-getter and wicket-taker against the USA respectively.

Zahoor Khan finished as the second-highest wicket-taker (41) for the UAE in the recently concluded WC League 2. He has already started the ongoing tournament with a bang, by picking three wickets in the opening game.

In the same tournament, Monak Patel scored the most runs (1,219 runs at 37) for the USA. In the process, he slammed two centuries and eight fifties. He also averages 37 versus the UAE.

Aaron Jones (294 runs at 59) and Saurabh Netravalkar (12 wickets) are the leading run-getter and wicket-taker respectively against theUAE.

Besides accumulating 874 runs at 26, Steven Taylor picked 32 wickets and grabbed 18 catches in WC League 2.

Karthik Meiyappan’s spin bowling has been causing plenty of problems for the opposition recently. Operating in the middle overs, he has bagged 16 wickets for the year including two four-fors and as many three-fors.

Ali Khan shot to fame by picking wickets with new and old ball in franchise T20 cricket. He has already taken five for the tournament in only two outings.

Aayan Afzal Khan (153 runs and eight wickets) is the only player from either side to feature in the Best11 for five consecutive ODIs.
